{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17654776","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17654776"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:56:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:56:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18633"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18633","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18633"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.96,0.04,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11365"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78397"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11365","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11365"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18633"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63759"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6809"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26378"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26681"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78397","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78397"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe lungs are divided into distinct lobes by fissures in the pleural surface. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the anatomical arrangement of lung lobes?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Both lungs have three lobes","Right lung has three lobes and left lung consists of two lobes","Right lung has two lobes and left lung has three lobes","Both lungs have four lobes","Both lungs have two lobes"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct arrangement is that the \u003Cstrong\u003Eright lung has three lobes and left lung has two lobes\u003C/strong\u003E. The right lung is divided into upper, middle and lower lobes by two fissures: the oblique and horizontal fissures. The left lung has only upper and lower lobes separated by the oblique fissure.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBoth lungs have three lobes\u003C/strong\u003E - Only the right lung has three lobes; the left lung has two lobes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERight lung has two lobes and left lung has three lobes\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the opposite of the correct arrangement\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBoth lungs have four lobes\u003C/strong\u003E - Neither lung has four lobes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBoth lungs have two lobes\u003C/strong\u003E - While the left lung has two lobes, the right lung has three lobes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe left lung has fewer lobes to accommodate the heart in the cardiac notch. The oblique fissure is present in both lungs, while the horizontal fissure is only present in the right lung.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The right lung has three lobes (upper, middle, lower) while the left lung has two lobes (upper, lower).","The oblique fissure separates upper and lower lobes in both lungs, while the horizontal fissure separates upper and middle lobes only in the right lung.","The left lung has a cardiac notch to accommodate the heart."],"references":["Chaudhry R, Bordoni B. Anatomy, Thorax, Lungs [Internet]. National Library of Medicine. StatPearls Publishing; 2019. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK470197/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","i